title: A1706 820-00923-A
message:
Hi, 
I have an A1706 820-00923-A, that had liquid contact (can't see any signs of it, but client says that has droped a few drops of water on the keyboard).
The laptop powers on, but can see the SSD, and the touch bar doesn't work.
I get 0V on PPVIN_2V7NAND_LB, and i assume that it is because of that the ssd doesn't work. I've checked the test point near R9350, but everithing looks ok in that area (actualy i can't see no signs of corrosion anywhere , except a bit in the BL C8500).

Where should i start? Can you help?

title: A1706 820-00923-A
message:
Touchbar doesn't work because needs to load its firmware from SSD.
So you should to fix SSD issue, if possible.

"I get 0V on PPVIN_2V7NAND_LB"
Bad contact on J9600?

title: A1706 820-00923-A
message:
Hi, it was a bit of dirt on  J9600.  After cleaning with IPA it started to work again.
Thanks!
